quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
37,1,"By those who range themselves in rows;"
37,2,"by those who reprove severely,"
37,3,"and those who recite the Exhortation; {1}",footnotes:1:The majority of the commentators agree that all these three groups imply the groups of the angels
37,4,"surely your God is One, {1}",footnotes:1:This is the truth to impress which an oath has been taken by the angels bearing the above-mentioned qualities. In other words
37,5,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and of whatever lies between the two, the Lord {1} of the Easts. {2}",footnotes:1:The truth that has been conveyed in these verses is: The Master and Ruler of the Universe is the Real Deity of men. He alone can be
37,6,"We have adorned the lower heaven with the adornment of the stars {1}",footnotes:1:“Lower heaven”: The nearest heaven which can be seen with the naked eye
37,7,"and have protected it from every rebellious satan. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,8,"These satans cannot listen to what transpires in the High Council for they are pelted away from every side"
37,9,"and are repelled. Theirs is an unceasing chastisement."
37,10,"And if any is able to snatch a fragment, he is pursued by a piercing flame. {1}",footnotes:1:To understand this one should keep in view the fact that
37,11,"So ask them (that is, human beings): “Were they harder to create than the objects We created?” {1} We created them from sticky clay. {2}",footnotes:1:This is an answer to the suspicions of the disbelievers of Makkah
37,12,"You marvel (at the wondrous creations of Allah) and they scoff at it,"
37,13,"and when they are admonished, they pay no heed;"
37,14,"and if they see any Sign, they laugh it away"
37,15,"and say: “This is nothing but plain sorcery. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,16,"Is it ever possible that after we die and are reduced to dust and (a skeleton of) bones, we will be raised to life?"
37,17,"And so also shall our forefathers of yore be raised to life?”"
37,18,"Tell them: “Yes; and you are utterly helpless (against Allah).” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,19,"There will be a single stern rebuff and lo, they will be observing with their own eyes (all that they had been warned against). {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,20,"They will then say: “Woe for us. This is the Day of Judgement.”"
37,21,"“Yes, this is the Day of Final Decision that you used to deny as a lie.” {1}",footnotes:1:It may be that this is said by the believers
37,22,"(Then will the command be given): “Muster all the wrong-doers {1} and their spouses {2} and the deities whom they used to serve",footnotes:1:The word “azwaj” in the original text might also imply their wives
37,23,"apart from Allah, {1} and direct them to the path of Hell,",footnotes:1:“gods” here implies two kinds of the gods.
37,24,"and detain them there; they will be called to account."
